<br>
Previously, the MOST spells/effects/buffs a player or monster could have at any one time was 15.<br>
<br>
They are increasing this on test to 30..<br>
<br>
As for the DoT stacking: previously only ONE casting of a spell could be on a player or monster (ie: you cannot have wolf form AND SoW on at the same time, as well, you cannot have two different people cast SoW on you and move at super-fast speeds).<br>
<br>
Now, they are allowing DoTs of the same name (and same spell line) to be &quot;stacked&quot;.<br>
<br>
ie: As a 26 druid, my best DoT is called Creeping Crud. Previously, If I was grouped with another druid and I cast Creeping Crud on the monster, and then the other druid tried casting Creeping Crud on the monster, it would inform him that the spell did not take hold since I had allready cast Creeping Crud on the monster.<br>
<br>
NOW though, We can both cast it on the mob (well, on the test server anyhow). So the monster would have TWO instances of Creeping Crud on him. So instead of losing 210hp over 10 ticks, he would be losing 420hp over the duration of the DoTs. <p>Velyn<br />
